text:
Bug 19229 is also apparent on Solaris 7 for 2.0.46.
exports.c is not properly generated and massive amounts of apr redefinitions 
are reported halting the compile.
Interestingly enough exports.c is correctly generated on Solaris 9.

text:

around to get it to compile.

text:
When I took symlinks out of the equation and compiled in /tmp I was able to get 
it to work.
Previously my home dir where I did my compiles was a symlink.
Symlinks or something like that is throwing something off.
